**Thank you for remaining a member of the Manchester YMCA Harriers!**

Following the tough conditions experienced at the Kentmere Horsehoe Fell Race last year, we’ve organised a navigation course for those who expressed an interest in improving their navigation and navigational techniques.

The course will be led by experienced personal trainers [Lynne Taylor](http://www.globaltherapies.com/about-us/lynne-taylor/) and [Tim Budd](http://www.globaltherapies.com/about-us/tim-budd/), from Glossop based Global Therapies.

The date is set for Saturday 20 July, and we expect to start at 9:00am from Old Glossop and finish around 3:00pm. We’ll try to coordinate lifts / travelling together by train.

There will be lots of standing while instruction takes place and everyone learns, and we will move at walking pace in between.

If the weather is bad/rainy/windy the course will still go ahead - unless it is _unprecedentedly_ bad weather.

## Required Equipment 

We will be in an area where weather conditions can change very quickly, so you will need to bring clothes to suit; i.e. **appropriate footwear**, **multiple layers** and **waterproofs** - even if the weather forecast is good.

We will eat lunch on the hill so you'll also need to bring **food and drink** for the day.

You will also need the **Ordnance Survey OL1 (Dark Peak Area) map** and **a compass**. You are advised to get a [laminated version of the map](https://dash4it.co.uk/catalog/product/view/id/8680/s/act-1-the-peak-district-dark-peak-area/), as the paper ones tend to get badly damaged in even light rain.

